cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO 

The paper deals with building biological models using computational methods, specifically Answer Set Programming (ASP). ASP is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to automate the process of building biological models. The paper also mentions the use of databases (cs.DB) to store and retrieve experimental data. Additionally, the paper falls under the subfield of Quantitative Biology (q-bio), specifically in the subcategories of Quantitative Methods (QM) and Tissues and Organs (TO), as it deals with building models to understand biological systems.
